@startuml
title game-lib sounds: audio utilities overview

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<exported>> #E8F5E9
  BackgroundColor<<utility>> #F7F7F7
  BackgroundColor<<runtime>> #FFF3E0
  BackgroundColor<<external>> #E8F1FF
}

package "src/lib/sounds" {
  component "pingPongBeep(...)" as Ping <<exported>>
  component "ricochetSound(...)" as Ricochet <<exported>>
  component "Procedural SFX routine\n(short-lived beep synthesis)" as Sfx <<utility>>
  component "Sound parameters\nfrequency, duration,\nvolume, envelope" as Params <<utility>>
}

package "Typical call sites" {
  component "Game / Stage callbacks" as Lifecycle <<runtime>>
  component "Entity / behavior logic" as Gameplay <<runtime>>
}

cloud "Browser Web Audio API" {
  component "AudioContext" as AudioContext <<external>>
  component "OscillatorNode" as Oscillator <<external>>
  component "GainNode" as Gain <<external>>
  component "AudioDestinationNode" as Destination <<external>>
}

package "Separate subsystem\n(not used directly here)" {
  component "AssetManager\nsrc/lib/core/loaders" as AssetManager
  component "Loaded audio assets\nbuffer playback path" as AssetPipeline
}

Lifecycle --> Ping : invoke
Gameplay --> Ping : invoke
Lifecycle --> Ricochet : invoke
Gameplay --> Ricochet : invoke

Ping --> Params : choose ping-pong profile
Ricochet --> Params : choose ricochet profile

Ping --> Sfx : delegate
Ricochet --> Sfx : delegate

Sfx --> AudioContext : create per call
Sfx --> Oscillator : configure tone
Sfx --> Gain : shape volume envelope
Oscillator --> Gain : connect
Gain --> Destination : connect to output
AudioContext --> Destination : owns

AssetManager --> AssetPipeline : manages cached assets

note right of Sfx
Standalone procedural audio helper.

Current role:
- create a fresh audio context
- create oscillator + gain nodes
- apply a very short envelope
- emit a tiny synthesized sound effect
end note

note bottom of AssetManager
The sound helpers in `src/lib/sounds`
are separate from the centralized asset-loading path.
They do not depend on cached audio files to play.
end note

note bottom of Ping
High-level helper for a short
arcade-style beep.
end note

note bottom of Ricochet
High-level helper for a short
impact / ricochet effect.
end note

legend right
|= Area |= Role |
| `src/lib/sounds` | small procedural sound utilities |
| Web Audio API | browser playback primitives |
| Asset pipeline | separate loaded-audio path |
endlegend

@enduml
